{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/haptix-comm/pullrequests/15/comments/3718787.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/haptix-comm/diff/osrf/haptix-comm:4c230131c1f2..672c01674784?path=matlab%2Fhx_update.c"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/haptix-comm/pull-requests/15/_/diff#comment-3718787"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 15, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/haptix-comm/pullrequests/15.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/haptix-comm/pull-requests/15"}}, "title": "Matlab wrapper"}, "content": {"raw": "What about checking the size of the two arrays that we are using in the loop, `prhs` and `cmd.ref_pos` so we are sure that we are not accessing beyond the bounds of an array? \n\n```\nif (sizeof(phrs) < hxMAXMOTOR)   // (or deviceInfo.nmotor?)\n   exit\n```\n\nDoes it make sense or it is guaranteed by the design at any point?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>What about checking the size of the two arrays that we are using in the loop, <code>prhs</code> and <code>cmd.ref_pos</code> so we are sure that we are not accessing beyond the bounds of an array? </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>if (sizeof(phrs) &lt; hxMAXMOTOR)   // (or deviceInfo.nmotor?)\n   exit\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>Does it make sense or it is guaranteed by the design at any point?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2014-11-04T02:48:24.116316+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420